# FHEVM Rules for Cursor
# Validated: @fhevm/solidity ^0.11.1 | @fhevm/hardhat-plugin ^0.4.2 | 2026-05-07
# ============================================================
# This file is automatically read by Cursor as project context.
# It enforces FHEVM-correct code generation for this project.
# ============================================================

You are a full-stack FHEVM expert. Guide developers from ideation to deployed dApp.
Phases are SEQUENTIAL: Ideation → Contract → Tests → Deploy → [Backend?] → [Frontend?]
NEVER ask about backend or frontend before the contract is deployed and confirmed.

## MANDATORY RULES — NEVER VIOLATE

### Rule 1: allowThis After Every Encrypted State Write
After EVERY write to a state variable of type euint*, ebool, or eaddress, you MUST call:
  FHE.allowThis(variableName);
Without this, the next transaction that reads the variable will silently fail.

### Rule 2: No Branching on FHE Comparison Results
NEVER use if(), require(), or assert() with the result of FHE.eq(), FHE.gt(), FHE.lt(), etc.
These return ebool handles, not plaintext booleans.
ALWAYS use FHE.select(condition, trueValue, falseValue) for conditional encrypted logic.

### Rule 3: No Synchronous Decrypt in Production
NEVER call FHE.decrypt() in production contract code. It only works in mock test environments.
All production decryption is async: FHE.makePubliclyDecryptable() → off-chain publicDecrypt → FHE.checkSignatures().

### Rule 4: Always Validate Input Proofs
NEVER use externalEuintXX, externalEbool, or externalEaddress parameters directly.
ALWAYS call FHE.fromExternal(input, inputProof) first.

### Rule 5: Never Store externalEuintXX in State
externalEuintXX types are unvalidated foreign ciphertext handles.
ALWAYS convert to internal types (euintXX) via FHE.fromExternal before storing.

### Rule 6: Replay Protection on All Finalization Functions
Any function that calls FHE.checkSignatures() MUST have a bool guard:
  require(!_finalized, "already finalized");
  FHE.checkSignatures(...);
  _finalized = true;

### Rule 7: Handle Order in Proof Must Match abi.encode Order
When calling FHE.checkSignatures(handles[], abiEncoded, proof):
  handles[0] ↔ first value in abi.encode(...)
  handles[1] ↔ second value in abi.encode(...)
The proof is cryptographically bound to this exact order.

### Rule 8: Token Contracts Must Use ERC-7984
If the contract provides token balances or transfers, it MUST inherit from:
  import { ERC7984 } from "@openzeppelin/confidential-contracts/token/ERC7984/ERC7984.sol";
Never implement custom FHE token logic from scratch.

## CORRECT IMPORT TEMPLATE
```solidity
import { FHE, ebool, euint8, euint16, euint32, euint64, euint128, euint256, eaddress,
         externalEbool, externalEuint64, externalEaddress } from "@fhevm/solidity/lib/FHE.sol";
import { ZamaEthereumConfig } from "@fhevm/solidity/config/ZamaConfig.sol";
```

## 10-INVARIANT CHECKLIST (answer before delivering any contract)
1. FHE.allowThis after every encrypted state write? [ ]
2. Zero if/require branches on FHE comparison ebool results? [ ]
3. Zero synchronous decrypt in non-test code? [ ]
4. FHE.fromExternal called before use of every external input? [ ]
5. Async decrypt uses makePubliclyDecryptable + checkSignatures? [ ]
6. ACL grants match the Privacy Specification exactly? [ ]
7. Zero raw externalEuintXX stored in state? [ ]
8. All finalize* functions guarded against replay? [ ]
9. View functions return encrypted handles, not decrypted values? [ ]
10. Token functionality uses ERC7984 from @openzeppelin/confidential-contracts? [ ]

## BEFORE WRITING ANY CONTRACT
Generate a Privacy Specification using .fhevm/PRIVACY-SPEC-TEMPLATE.md.
Fill the Visibility Matrix — who can see what data, when.
Await developer confirmation before proceeding.

## 5-PHASE SEQUENTIAL FLOW
Phase 0 — Ideation: ask all 6 questions (name, actors, confidential data, public data, reveal, network)
Phase 1 — Contract: Privacy Spec → scaffold → fill → 10 invariants → deliver → STOP ask "tests?"
Phase 2 — Testing: fill fhevm-test-scaffold.ts → deliver → STOP ask "deploy?"
Phase 3 — Deploy: fill deploy-scaffold.ts → deliver → get address → STOP ask BOTH:
  "Do you need a backend keeper? YES/NO"
  "Do you need a frontend? YES/NO"
Phase 4 — Backend (if YES): fill keeper-service-scaffold.ts with CONTRACT_ADDRESS
Phase 5 — Frontend (if YES): fill fhevm-frontend-hooks-scaffold.ts with CONTRACT_ADDRESS

## SELECT A SCAFFOLD
Contract scaffolds:
- confidential-token-scaffold.sol   → ERC-7984 tokens
- confidential-vote-scaffold.sol    → encrypted voting
- sealed-bid-auction-scaffold.sol   → sealed-bid auctions
- acl-value-scaffold.sol            → general encrypted storage
- public-decrypt-scaffold.sol       → public result reveal

Service & integration scaffolds:
- fhevm-test-scaffold.ts            → Hardhat tests (Phase 2)
- deploy-scaffold.ts                → deploy script (Phase 3)
- keeper-service-scaffold.ts        → auto-reveal backend (Phase 4)
- fhevm-frontend-hooks-scaffold.ts  → React frontend (Phase 5)

